Mac Install python 2.7 and python 3 on mac.
Step1: Install pyenv
    $ brew install pyenv
Step2: Enable pyenv in Bash
    $ vim ~/.bash_profile
    add: eval "$(pyenv init -)"
Step3: pyenv install python
    $ pyenv install 2.7.*
    $ pyenv install 3.6.*
Step4: check pyenv versions
    $ pyenv versions
Step5: set global python version
    $ pyenv global 3.6.*
Step6: set local python version in current directory
    $ pyenv local 2.7.*
Step7: check the python version
    $ python --version
